name: An Abstract Fancy
description:
Elegant. Clusters. Statement. Abstract.

Handcrafted metal cuff bracelet contains 48 different beads made of glass, swarovski crystals, wood, plastic, metal and faux pearls.

The cuff measures 6 inches on the inside with a 1 inch open gap between the ends of the cuff. The cuff is very forgiving in regards to size. The cuff can be bent outwards or inwards to fit any size wrist.

name: Delightful
description:
Bright and Beautiful.

Upon this necklace, rest 34 beads, all of different materials, shapes, sizes and colors. Materials such as glass, plastic, metal, wood, faux pearls and swarovski crystals. The beads are strung on heavy duty nylon coated metal wire. The wire is woven with and alternating method of bead, then chain. The chain is a small silver metal chain link.


The necklace measures 7.5 inches when the clasp is closed and measure from the back of the neck to the longest part of the necklace. It is to be worn as a choker, but is not tight on the neck. When measured from tip to tip it measures almost 16 inches.

name: The Perfect Pearl Necklace
description:
Glamorous. Glitzy. Adorable.

Simply put, this necklace is sure to brighten your look. While classy and luxurious, this necklace is equally cute and kitschy. 

This is and ultra vintage, ascending faux pearl necklace.

The beads are white plastic, not glass, and are the perfect addition to any outfit, formal or everyday. 

The necklace measures 9 inches in length and the plastic, white faux pearls are strung on a sturdy white beading twine.

The clasp is classified as a box clasp. Though this is no ordinary clasp. The box clasp is an ornate bow tie with faux gems, and is missing one gem in one corner of the bow tie. 

CLASP INSTRUCTIONS:
The folded metal spring or lever slips into the hole in the box with the end of the lever sticking out. The compressed spring holds the two ends in place. It is released by pressing the two ends of the lever together and pulling it out of the bow tie.

There is writing on the back of the bow tie clasp that says "Japan," thus this costume jewelry was fabricated in Japan.
